Tomcat:
    - Default embedded server in Spring Boot applications.
    - Supports servlets, JSP, and WebSocket.
    - Better suited for production-grade applications.
======================================================================================================
* Spring Boot supports embedded servers like Tomcat, Jetty, and Undertow.
Benefits:
    - No need for external server setup.
    - Simplified deployment â€” just run a JAR file (java -jar app.jar).
    - Consistent environment for testing and production.
======================================================================================================
* How to change the default port:
You can change the default port by setting the property in application.properties
server.port=8081
======================================================================================================
